==IFPI best-selling single worldwide by year==
The charts of the best-selling singles by year in the world are compiled by the [[International Federation of the Phonographic Industry]] annually since 2007. These charts were published in their two annual reports, the ''Digital Music Report'' and the ''Recording Industry in Numbers''. Both the ''Digital Music Report'' and the ''Recording Industry in Numbers'' were replaced in 2016 by the ''Global Music Report''.<ref>{{cite web|title= Digital Music Report / Recording Industry in Numbers |url= http://www.ifpi.org/digital-music-report.php |publisher= [[International Federation of the Phonographic Industry]] |accessdate= 14 April 2018}}</ref>

Units sold include [[Music download|single-track downloads]], audio and video [[Truetone|mastertones]], [[ringback tone]]s, full track downloads to mobile and, starting in 2013, [[Streaming media|track-equivalent streams]]. All versions of the same song are combined in these charts.

